Kassiopeia - a tracking simulation package from the KATRIN collaboration

Licensing and Warranty:
	See https://katrin-experiment.github.io/Kassiopeia/license.html

Authors:
	See https://katrin-experiment.github.io/Kassiopeia/authors.html

User's Guide:
	Documentation can be found in the user's guide available at:
	https://katrin-experiment.github.io/Kassiopeia/

Bugs:
	In the surely unlikely event that you find a bug, it may be submitted to the
	Kassiopeia bug tracker at:
	https://github.com/KATRIN-Experiment/Kassiopeia/issues

Reference:
	To cite the use of and/or data produced with the assistance of Kassiopeia or its associated libraries (KGeoBag, KEMField, or Kommon), please refer to the paper:
	D. Furse et al. (2017) New J. Phys. 19 053012: “Kassiopeia: A Modern, Extensible C++ Particle Tracking Package” (doi:10.1088/1367-2630/aa6950)
